Source: vignettes/modules.Rmd
modules.Rmd

Introduction

Shinytdmore helps you build an application for dose adaptation. This vignette will take you through the application step-by-step.

Application definition

library(shinytdmore)

dir <- tempfile()
dir.create(dir)
db <- FileDatabase$new(dir)

ui <- shinyTdmoreUI(title="shinyTDMore",
                    patientsTabUI(id="patientsTabId"),
                    predictionTabUI(id="predictionTabId"),
                    modelTabUI(id="modelTabId"),
                    reportsTabUI(id="reportsTabId"),
                    aboutTabUI(id="aboutTabId"))

conf <- list(save=list(module=saveProject, id="saveProjectId"),
             new_patient=list(module=newPatientDialog, id="newPatientDialogId"),
             patients=list(module=patientsTab, id="patientsTabId"),
             prediction=list(module=predictionTab, id="predictionTabId"),
             model=list(module=modelTab, id="modelTabId"),
             reports=list(module=reportsTab, id="reportsTabId"),
             about=list(module=aboutTab, id="aboutTabId"))

server <- function(input, output, session) {
  shinyTdmore(input, output, session, conf, db)
}

shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)

Patient selection screen

Sys.sleep(2)
file <- knitr::fig_path("png")
app$takeScreenshot(file)
knitr::include_graphics(file)

Create new patient

app$setInputs(`patientsTabId-newPatientButton`="click")
Sys.sleep(2)
file <- knitr::fig_path("png")
app$takeScreenshot(file)
knitr::include_graphics(file)

app$setInputs(`newPatientDialogId-firstname`="Ruben", `newPatientDialogId-lastname`="Faelens")
app$setInputs(`newPatientDialogId-modalFormOK`="click")
Sys.sleep(2)
file <- knitr::fig_path("png")
app$takeScreenshot(file)
knitr::include_graphics(file)

Prediction screen

link <- app$findElement(linkText='Ruben Faelens')
link$click()
Sys.sleep(10)
#app$getDebugLog()
file <- knitr::fig_path("png")
app$takeScreenshot(file)
knitr::include_graphics(file)

Prediction graph

app$setInputs(`predictionTabId-next_plot` = "click")

knitr::include_graphics(file)
